GC-MS are listed in Table 1. The gas chromatographs obtained
from GC-MS analyses of oil extracted using solvent and SFE are
shown in Figures 1–4. In total, 41 constituents were identified
in the essential oils obtained from Iranian and Indian
seeds by using SFE and solvent extraction techniques.
In general, the oil extraction efficiency obtained from
SFE was higher than the extracted yield achieved by solvent
extraction technique. Among the main compounds identified
by GC-MS, LA (22.4%–61.85%) was the main fatty acid in
oils extracted by both SFE and solvent extraction
